adjectives.description: asquirm (comparative more asquirm, superlative most asquirm)

examples: But a fish-market, even at Rialto  […]  is only a fish-market after all: it is wet and slimy under foot, and the innumerable gigantic eels, writhing everywhere, set the soul asquirm, and soon-sated curiosity slides willingly away.
an aquarium all asquirm with trout and gold fish
